Ondo State governor Oluwarotimi Akeredolu (SAN) has approved the appointment of Folajimi Olasehinde-Vicente as his Senior Special Assistant (SSA) on Diaspora Affairs. A Statement by his Chief Press Secretary (CPS), Mr. Segun Ajiboye, said  the appointment takes immediate effect. Mrs. Folajimi Olasehinde-Vicente, a lawyer,  is the Yeyemofin of Idogun in Ose local government area of the state She is also the former lawmaker representing Ose Constituency. Akeredolu congratulated the new appointee as she joined his administration to further push forward the efforts aimed at developing the Sunshine State.